Alt + Shift + 1

// Show whitespace characters in Visual Studio Code
"editor.renderWhitespace": "all",

// vertical rule VS code (PEP 8 Python [80])
File > Preferences > settings
"editor.rulers": [79]

Ctrl + Shift +H - global replace
Ctrl + Shift + N - open new VScode
Shift + F12 - information on the use of the component. Where class this import and use
Ctrl + space - autocomplete html code
Ctrl + B - hide left menu
Ctrl + Shift + I - formation json
Ctrl + X - delete line
F12 - debug element in VScode

// watch for file changes in this large workspace (/etc/sysctl.conf)
fs.inotify.max_user_watches=524288
sudo sysctl -p

// Toogle line comment => Keyboard Shortcuts => ctrl+/

// user config VS code.Delete white space after save;
files.trimTrailingWhitespace": false,

----------------------------------------------Settings Sync

install Settings Sync  Ctrl+ Shift + P write "sync Update/Upload Settings" is generate
token in console or redirect to git to create gist with token after
then we insert in VScode. Settings Upload.

In new machine we only Ctrl+ Shift + P write "sync Download settings" insert in
VScode "GitHub Gist" after then insert "GitHub ID"(ID in URL- numbers). We are waiting for
downloading all extensions. Restart VScode.

//watches add in /etc/sysctl.conf => fs.inotify.max_user_watches=524288
echo fs.inotify.max_user_watches=524288 | sudo tee -a /etc/sysctl.conf && sudo sysctl -p

